oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Grocery store belonging to Grover Cleveland Sherrod
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of the interior of a grocery store belonging to Grover Cleveland Sherrod. He is pictured along with an unidentified man.

Grover Cleveland Sherrod was born on February 22, 1890 in Gift, Mississippi. He was a graduate of Cumberland Law School and became a lawyer. He was appointed US District Attorney General for the 13th District. He died on December 20, 1952 and is buried at the Memphis National Cemetery.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
